        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(qa): crabline channel driver",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR makes QA profile channel drivers executable and separates channel identity from transport mode.\n\n- Adds the merged `crabline` package as a QA Lab dependency pinned to `openclaw/crabline@93b4de9b933b2c32f16f265725a0af3c429997e2`.\n- Runs the `smoke-ci` QA profile through the Crabline runtime via `import(\"crabline\")`, with `channel: telegram` and other requested channel IDs resolved through Crabline instead of an inlined local fallback.\n- Adds a separate `QA Smoke CI` PR workflow for the canonical mock-channel smoke profile.\n- Keeps `.github/workflows/qa-live-transports-convex.yml` focused on scheduled/manual live transport coverage.\n- Makes the `release` live profile fan out to the native Matrix, Telegram, Discord, Slack, and WhatsApp live lane catalogs, then merges their `qa-evidence.json` outputs into one profile evidence artifact.\n\n## Why\n\nTests should be able to ask for a channel shape such as `telegram` while the selected profile decides whether that exchange is handled by Crabline or by a real live transport. `smoke-ci` is the PR CI mock-channel profile. Live service coverage stays in the live transport lanes and release profile evidence.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check .github/workflows/qa-live-transports-convex.yml .github/workflows/qa-smoke-ci.yml docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md extensions/qa-lab/package.json pnpm-workspace.yaml extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec tsgo --noEmit -p tsconfig.extensions.json`\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.test.ts test/scripts/package-acceptance-workflow.test.ts`",
